  "prompt": "How hard is it to crack IIT?",
  "response": "Cracking the Indian Institutes of Technology (IIT) entrance exam, known as the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE), is considered extremely challenging. Here are several reasons why:\n\n1. **High Competition**: With hundreds of thousands of students applying each year, and only a few thousand seats available in the IITs, the level of competition is incredibly high.\n\n2. **Difficulty Level**: The JEE exam is known for its difficult questions that test a deep understanding of physics, chemistry, and mathematics. The questions require not only rote learning but also sharp problem-solving skills and the ability to apply concepts in unique ways.\n\n3. **Syllabus and Breadth**: The syllabus is extensive and covers a wide range of topics from the Class 11 and 12 curriculum, requiring a deep and thorough understanding of each topic.\n\n4. **Intensive Preparation**: Successful candidates often undergo several years of intensive coaching and preparation, dedicating many hours each day to study. Many students attend specialized coaching institutes to better prepare for the JEE.\n\n5. **Pressure and Stress**: The exam process can be stressful because of the high stakes involved. Performance in the JEE can significantly impact educational and career opportunities.\n\n6. **Multiple Stages**: The exam is held in two stages: JEE Main and JEE Advanced. Only those who rank within a specific cut-off in the JEE Main are eligible to take the JEE Advanced.\n\nDespite these challenges, with dedication, strategic preparation, and time management, students can overcome these hurdles. Many aspirants find success through disciplined study schedules, regular practice, and by taking advantage of available resources such as books, online courses, and coaching institutes.",
